cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark in your research, please cite as below."
type: software

title: "GeneLab Benchmark: A Multi-Tissue Spaceflight Transcriptomics Benchmark for AI/ML Models"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-03-01"

abstract: >
  GeneLab Benchmark is a public benchmark for evaluating AI and machine learning
  models on NASA OSDR (Open Science Data Repository) mouse spaceflight transcriptomics
  data. It provides standardized Leave-One-Mission-Out (LOMO) cross-validation splits,
  baseline model implementations, and an evaluation framework for multi-tissue
  spaceflight detection tasks (Category A) and cross-mission transfer tasks (Category B).
  Tissues include gastrocnemius, thymus, skin, liver, kidney, and eye/retina.

